{
  "description": "Experiment-row chunk assembly: args → the {type:\"dataset\"} WireChunk both runners emit per dataset item. Pins TS `datasetRowToWire` (prompt-core/src/wire.ts) and Python `_dataset_row_to_wire` (prompt_core/webhook_runner.py) to ONE canonical shape. Absence semantics (the drift this vector was created to catch — Python used to emit `\"expectedOutput\": null` where TS omitted the key): expectedOutput / actualOutput / tokens are OMITTED when missing from args, never null; traceId is omitted when missing OR empty-string; evals is ALWAYS present (possibly []). Comparison is on parsed JSON (key-order-agnostic). Changing any expected value is a wire-format break for the experiments UI AND a cross-language break — treat as semver-major.",
